rows.title: Solo Leveling Character Creator
rows.titleText: Solo Leveling character creator.  This is a meta CYOA where you create your character for the Solo Leveling CYOA.

rows.title: Body
rows.titleText: This is where you create your body.  You decide your starting age, race, height, gender and appearance.

rows.title: Gender
rows.titleText: This is where you choose your gender.

rows.title: Age
rows.titleText: This is where you decide the age at which your regain consciousness if you insert or the age you appear as if you chose drop in.

objects.title: Child
objects.text: This is any age 12 and under.

objects.title: Teanager
objects.text: This is any age between 13 and 18.

objects.title: Adult
objects.text: This is any age between 19 and 60

objects.title: Elderly
objects.text: This is any age over 60.

rows.title: Race
rows.titleText: This is where you decide what race you want to be.  If you choose 2 races then you become a hybrid of said races.

objects.title: Human
objects.text: This makes you a human from the world of Solo Leveling.  The human race does not have a ruling Monarch.

objects.title: Demon
objects.text: This race makes you a Demon from solo leveling.  Some notable Demons are Vulcan, Metus, and Esil Radiru.  The Demons are ruled over by the Monarch of White Flames.

objects.title: Snow Folk
objects.text: This race makes you a Snow Folk from Solo Leveling.  This includes Snow Elves, Yetis, Ice Bears, Ice Golems, Ice Trolls, and Ice Kobolds.  The Snow Folk are ruled over by the Monarch of Frost

objects.title: Monstrous Humanoid
objects.text: This race turn you into a Monstrous Humanoid form Solo Leveling.  This includes Trolls, Orcs, Goblins, and Kobolds.  Monstrous Humanoids are ruled over by the Monarch of Iron Body.

objects.title: Dragon
objects.text: This race turns you into a Dragon from Solo Leveling.  Notable Dragons are Kaisellin, Kamish, and Nagas.  This race is ruled over by the Monarch of Destruction

objects.title: Insect
objects.text: This race turns you into a insect from Solo Leveling.  This includes Giant Centipedes and Giant ants.  A notable Insect is Beru.  This race is ruled over by the Monarch of Plagues.

objects.title: Undead
objects.text: This race turns you into an Undead from Solo Leveling.  This includes Shadows, Liches, Skeletons, and Zombies.  This race is ruled over by the Monarch of Shadows.

objects.title: Titan
objects.text: This turns you into a Titan from Solo Leveling.  They survive off eating rocks form worlds that support life.  They have no ruling Monarch.

objects.title: Giant
objects.text: This turns you into a Giant from Solo Leveling.  We only know of normal Giants.  This race is ruled by the Monarch of the Beginning.

objects.title: Demonic Specter
objects.text: This turns you into a Demonic Specter from Solo Leveling.  We know nothing about Demonic Specters.  This race is ruled by the Monarch of Transfiguration.

objects.title: Other
objects.text: This turns you into a race that doesn't have a clear origin.  An example would be the Dwarfs Sung Jinwoo had as Shadows.

objects.title: Ruler Vessel
objects.text: This turns you into a Ruler Vessel.  A Ruler Vessel is someone with the blood of a Ruler in them. A Ruler Vessel is naturally stronger than normal people of their rank.

rows.title: Height
rows.titleText: This is where you decide how tall you want to be.

objects.title: Dwarfism
objects.text: This makes it so you suffer from Dwarfism.  This can cause some medical problems.

objects.title: Short
objects.text: This makes you shorter than the average person.

objects.title: Average
objects.text: This makes you about as tall as the average person.

objects.title: Tall
objects.text: This makes you taller than the average person.

objects.title: Gigantism
objects.text: This makes it so you suffer from Gigantism.  This can cause some medical problems.

rows.title: Appearance
rows.titleText: This is where you decide how you want your body to look like.

objects.title: Monstrous
objects.text: This makes you look like a monstrous being.  This will cause revulsion and disgust in those who see you.

objects.title: Ugly
objects.text: This makes you look worse than average.

objects.title: Average
objects.text: This makes you look average.

objects.title: Attractive
objects.text: This makes you look better than average.

objects.title: Perfection
objects.text: This makes you look perfect.  It causes an uncanny valley effect in those of your race.

rows.title: Class
rows.titleText: This is where you choose your class.  Each class offers different benefits.  They boost actions that align with the class.  The boosts scale with your rank.

objects.title: Fighter
objects.text: This choice locks you into the fighter class.  Fighters are hunters who specialize in melee combat and strike a balance between offence and defence.  The Fighter class scales with your rank.  The higher the rank the more the class boosts you.

objects.title: Mage
objects.text: This choice locks you into the Mage class.  Mages are hunters who specialize in sorcery and magic.  The Mage class scales with your rank.  The higher the rank the more the class boosts you.

objects.title: Ranger
objects.text: This choice locks you into the Ranger class.  Rangers are hunters who specialize in long ranged combat.  The Ranger class scales with your rank.  The higher the rank the more the class boosts you.

objects.title: Healer
objects.text: This choice locks you into the Healer class.  Healers are hunters who specialize in healing and support.  The Healer class scales with your rank.  The higher the rank the more the class boosts you.

objects.title: Tanker
objects.text: This choice locks you into the Tanker class.  Tankers are hunters who specialize in Defense.  The Tanker class scales with your rank.  The higher the rank the more the class boosts you.

objects.title: Assassin
objects.text: This choice locks you into the Assassin class.  Assassins are hunters who specialize in both speed and close ranged combat.  The Assassin class scales with your rank.  The higher the rank the more the class boosts you.

rows.title: Fighter
rows.titleText: This is where you choose your class specialization.

objects.title: Weapon Master
objects.text: The Weapon Master specialization focuses on using powerful weapons and dealing damage.  This specialization focuses on weapon mastery and gear.

objects.title: Magic Fighter
objects.text: The Magic Fighter specialization focuses on mixing magic with close quarters combat.  This specialization uses elemental magic to buff their armor and weapons.

objects.title: Jester
objects.text: The Jester specialization focuses on using tricks and their surroundings in a fight.  This specialization uses poison, hidden weapons, and acrobatics to constantly move around and harass their enemies.

rows.title: Mage
rows.titleText: This is where you choose your mage specialization.

objects.title: Elemental
objects.text: The Elemental specialization focuses on controlling a basic element of your choice.  You can create, control, and destroy said element using your magic.

objects.title: Summoner
objects.text: The summoner specialization focuses on summoning minions to fight for you.  Your minions rank is decided by your rank.  The minions cost magic power to summon and keep around.

objects.title: Hex
objects.text: The Hex specialization focuses on debuffing your enemies and providing damage over time.  They can poison enemies, make them take more damage, and even weaken enemy items.

rows.title: Ranger
rows.titleText: This is where you choose your Ranger specialization

objects.title: Pirate
objects.text: The Pirate specialization focuses on utilizing ranged weapons in close quarters combat.  This specialization utilizes melee weapons alongside pistols, hand crossbows, and bombs.

objects.title: Trap Master
objects.text: The Trap Master specialization focuses on using traps to fight enemies.  This specialization utilizes poisons, debuffs, and their surroundings in order to corner their enemies.

objects.title: Heavy Ranger
objects.text: The Heavy Ranger specialization focuses on using stationary ranged weapons in order to deal more damage.  This specialization utilizes Ballista's, canons, and missiles.

rows.title: Elemental
rows.titleText: This is where you choose what element you will have as an elemental mage.

rows.title: Summoner
rows.titleText: This is where you choose what type of summon you will use.

objects.title: Humanoid
objects.text: The humanoid summon can be anything that is humanoid.  Some examples humans, orcs, goblins, trolls, skeletons, and giants.

objects.title: Beast
objects.text: The Beast summon is anything that is Beast like in nature.  Some examples are Dire Wolfs, Giant Centipedes, and Sabretooth tigers.

objects.title: Monster
objects.text: The monster summon is anything that is mythical in nature.  Some examples are ghosts, dragons, phoenixes, hydras, and oni.

rows.title: Healer
rows.titleText: This is where you choose your Healer specialization.

objects.title: Priest
objects.text: The Priest specialization focuses on divine power.  They can use their divine power to heal others, buff others, purify poisons or disease, and get rid of debuffs.

objects.title: Alchemist
objects.text: The Alchemist specialization focuses on potion creation.  They can make healing potion, mana potions, or even poisons to cover your weapons.  They use the materials found in gates to do this.

objects.title: Crafter
objects.text: The Crafter specialization focuses on using materials found in gates to make items for hunters.  They make weapons, armor, ammo, and food.  They things they make can provide special bonuses when used or consumed.

rows.title: Tank
rows.titleText: This is where you choose your Tank Specialization.

objects.title: Paladin
objects.text: The Paladin specialization makes it so you are able to wield holy magic.  This specialization focuses on AOE versions of healing and protection spells while taking damage.

objects.title: Berserker
objects.text: The Berserker specialization makes it so you can withstand immense amounts pain.  This specialization focuses on dealing more damage the more you are injured.

objects.title: Beast
objects.text: The Beast specialization focuses on imitating monsters.  This specialization allow you to designate a monster and slowly learn weaker versions of its abilities.

rows.title: Assassin
rows.titleText: This is where you choose your Assassin specialization

objects.title: Poison
objects.text: The Poison specialization provides you the abilities to create and utilize many different poisons.  You also get an immunity to weak poisons.

objects.title: Ninja
objects.text: The Ninja specialization provides you the ability to be supernaturally stealthy.  Ninjas focus on up close kills using their weapons and short ranged tools.

objects.title: Spy
objects.text: The Spy specialization focuses on gathering information and scouting ahead in gates.  They have abilities that confuse enemies, hide themselves, and give them information.

rows.title: Drawbacks
rows.titleText: This is where you can choose drawbacks in order to gain more points to spend elsewhere.

objects.title: Outsider
objects.text:
This makes it so others can sense your outsider nature.  
1 purchase makes them wary of you.
2 purchases makes them repulsed by you.  
3 purchases makes them hate you.  
These are just their initial impressions of you.

objects.title: Unlucky
objects.text:
This makes it so that you are extremely unlucky.  
1 purchase is only non lethal inconveniences.  An example would be hitting every red light every time you drive or never winning any game of chance.
2 purchases activate Murphy's law.  This makes things turn deadly.  An example would be a pole falling on you while walking or a meteor falling from the sky to only hit you.

objects.title: Region Locked
objects.text: This makes it so you can't ever leave Earth.  No matter what you try you will always be teleported back to Earth.  Gates and Dungeons are still accessible as long as they stay connected to Earth.

objects.title: Fictional Gates
objects.text:
Choose a fictional world.  Now that world is also invading the Earth through dungeons alongside the Monarchs.
1 purchase is a easy world on par with Dr.Stone or The Walking Dead
2 purchases is a medium world on par with MHA or Harry Potter
3 purchases is a hard world on par with Naruto or Star wars
4 purchases is a impossible world on par with Warhammer 40k or SCP

objects.title: Double Gate
objects.text: This Drawback makes it so the first gate you enter will be a double gate.  You will forget about taking this drawbacks.

rows.title: Rank
rows.titleText: This is where you choose your starting rank and your max potential rank.  Ranks are decided at birth.  The only known ways to increase ones rank is through a second awakening or outside interference.  Ranks decide how powerful your abilities are.  Ranks also affect your base stats.

rows.title: Potential Rank
rows.titleText: This is where you decide what your maximum rank is.  Normal hunters are unable to grow beyond their starting rank.  if you buy a higher potential rank than your starting rank then that will be your second awakening.  if you buy a lower potential rank than you starting rank then you are the weakest person in your rank and will regress in rank over time until you reach the rank of your potential.

objects.title: Mortal
objects.text: You have no rank.  This makes it so your maximum achievable power is at the limits of normal humans.  The hunter association will not accept you as a hunter.

objects.title: E Rank
objects.text: This makes your maximum achievable rank E.  This is the lowest class of hunters.

objects.title: D Rank
objects.text: This makes your maximum achievable rank D.  This is the below average class of hunters.

objects.title: C Rank
objects.text: This makes your maximum achievable rank C.  This is the average level of hunters

objects.title: B Rank
objects.text: This makes your maximum achievable rank B.  This is the upper class of hunters.

objects.title: A Rank
objects.text: This makes your maximum achievable rank A.  This is at the level of elite hunters.

objects.title: S Rank
objects.text: This makes your maximum achievable rank S.  This is the limits of normal hunters.

objects.title: National Level
objects.text: This makes your maximum achievable rank National Level.  This if for hunters who have broken past the normal limits.

rows.title: Starting Rank
rows.titleText: This is where you choose your starting rank.  If you chose a rank lower than your potential that means you can undergo a second awakening.  If you chose mortal as your rank and have higher potential that means you have not yet awakened.  If you chose a rank higher than your potential that means you are the weakest of your rank and will regress in rank over time until you reach the rank of your potential.

objects.title: Mortal
objects.text: You have no rank.  This makes it so your starting point is at the limits of normal humans.  The hunter association will not accept you as a hunter.

objects.title: E Rank
objects.text: This makes it so your starting rank is E.  This is the lowest class of hunters.

objects.title: D Rank
objects.text: This makes it so your starting rank is D.  This is the below average class of hunters.

objects.title: C Rank
objects.text: This makes it so your starting rank is C.  This is the average level of hunters

objects.title: B Rank
objects.text: This makes it so your starting rank is B.  This is the upper class of hunters.

objects.title: A Rank
objects.text: This makes it so your starting rank is A.  This is at the level of elite hunters.

objects.title: S Rank
objects.text: This makes it so your starting rank is S.  This is the limits of normal hunters.

objects.title: National Level
objects.text: This makes your starting rank be at National Level.  This is for hunters who have broken past normal limits.

rows.title: Talents
rows.titleText: This is where you choose some basic talents to help you adjust to the world.

objects.title: Learning
objects.text: You have an enhanced memory and comprehension speed.  This will allow you to learn faster.  This will also allow you to focus more intently.

objects.title: Language
objects.text: This allows you to learn languages faster.  This will also allow you to understand other better and know what to say to get what you want.

objects.title: Survival
objects.text: This will allow you to handle the outdoors and survive by yourself more easily.  This will also get rid of the small inconveniences of the outdoors.

objects.title: Acting
objects.text: This allows you to control your emptions and have a perfect poker face.  You can lie easily and never stumble over your lies.  You also seem more trustworthy to others.

rows.title: Boons
rows.titleText: This is where you choose general boons to help you adjust to the world.

objects.title: Sustenance
objects.text: This boon makes it so you no longer need to eat or drink anything to survive.  You can still eat if you want to.

objects.title: Disease
objects.text: This boon protects you from any diseases that you may encounter.

objects.title: Sleep
objects.text: This boon makes it so you no longer need to sleep.  You can sleep at will if you want to sleep.

objects.title: Memory
objects.text: This boon gives you a perfect memory with infinite space.  It also allows you to have perfect recall for all your memories.
